description:
&lt;p&gt;This post is open to applications from registered mental health nurses, Social Workers, Physiotherapists and Occupational Therapists&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bolton Older Adult Community Mental Health Team are recruiting a band 7 Senior Practitioner/ Deputy Team Leader to join the leadership team to continue to deliver a safe, effective, high quality service to older adults with mental health conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will provide leadership, supervision and consultation with all professionals within the multi-disciplinary team and carry a small complex case load in addition to supporting the team manager in the daily aims and functions of the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for someone looking to challenge their own skills and leadership qualities, support the service development, make a positive contribution to supporting team members to fulfill their potential and continue to work with Older Adults who have a range of mental health needs alongside physical health conditions and social care needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Usual working hours will be 9am to 5 pm Monday to Friday but some out of hours work may be required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be required to participate on the divisional Bronze on call rota.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameEmma FaircloughJob titleTeam ManagerEmail addressemma.fairclough@gmmh.nhs.ukTelephone number01204 483771&lt;/p&gt;
